libsurl
------------------------------------------
libsurl is a library for generating short urls (using various online services
like tinyurl.com and bit.ly) suited to use where space is limited, such as in
status messages.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.34-6
  libcurl4-7.40.0-1
  libsurl-devel-0.7.2-1bl2
  libsurl0-0.7.2-1bl2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-1
  cygport-0.17.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-2
  libtool-2.4.5-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://libsurl.sf.net/

Canonical download:
  http://launchpad.net/libsurl/trunk/0.7/+download/libsurl-0.7.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libsurl-0.7.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libsurl-0.7.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libsurl-0.7.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsurl-0.7.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsurl0-0.7.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsurl-devel-0.7.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

